&= x(x+5) + 7(x+5).
\end{align*}
Further employing the distributive property and combining like terms, we get: 
\begin{align*}
x(x+5) + 7(x+5) &= x^2 + 5x + 7x+ 35\\
&= \boxed{x^2 + 12x + 35}.
\end{align*}

