 Denote the popularity of a toaster, or the number of customers buying it, as $p$, and the price of the toaster as $c$. According to Daniel's theory, $p$ and $c$ are inversely proportional, implying $(p)(c)=k$ for a constant $k$. Given $p=12$ when $c=500$, we find $k=(12)(500)=6000$. Therefore, when $c=750$, we have:
\begin{align*}
(p)(c)&=k
\\\Rightarrow\qquad (p)(750)&=6000
\\\Rightarrow\qquad p&=\frac{6000}{750}
\\ &=\boxed{8}.
\end{align*}
Hence, according to Daniel's theory, 8 customers would purchase the $\$750$ toaster.

