rewritten_answer:
 When Chewbacca loses a pack of cherry gum, the ratio of cherry gum pieces to grape gum pieces becomes $(20-x)/30$. If he gains 5 packs of grape gum instead, the ratio becomes $20/(30+5x)$. As these ratios are equal, we get:

\begin{align*}
\frac{20-x}{30} &= \frac{20}{30+5x} \quad\implies\\
(20-x)(30+5x) &= (30)(20) \quad\implies\\
(20-x)(5)(6+x) &= (30)(20).\end{align*}

Dividing both sides by 5 results in $$(20-x)(6+x) = (30)(4)$$and expanding the left side simplifies to $$120+14x -x^2 = 120.$$Therefore, $x^2-14x=0$, leading to $x(x-14)=0$. Since $x$ can't be 0, we conclude that $x=\boxed{14}$.

