The probability of John arriving while the train is at the station equals the ratio of the shaded region to the entire square. Dividing the axes into 60 units, the shaded area can be divided into a triangle with an area of $20\cdot 20/2=200$ square units and a parallelogram with an area of $20\cdot 40=800$ square units. The total square has an area of 3600 square units. The ratio is $1000/3600=\boxed{\frac{5}{18}}$.
